episodes.title: Smoke
episodes.plot: Jimmy struggles to cope with Chuck's tragic incident. Mike ponders his role at Madrigal. Howard makes a startling confession.

episodes.title: Breathe
episodes.plot: Jimmy seeks new employment. Gus navigates the fallout from Hector's collapse. Kim endeavors to support Jimmy in the wake of Chuck's death.

episodes.title: Something Beautiful
episodes.plot: Jimmy puts a risky plan into motion; as alliances shift, Nacho finds himself in the crosshairs; Kim contemplates her future.

episodes.title: Talk
episodes.plot: A restless Jimmy embarks on a new endeavor while Mike burns bridges; Kim pursues her bliss; Nacho tries to survive a turf war.

episodes.title: Quite a Ride
episodes.plot: Jimmy identifies a new market for his talents; Mike vets a potential partnership; Kim drives a hard bargain.

episodes.title: Piñata
episodes.plot: While Jimmy daydreams about reconstituting Wexler-McGill, Kim sets out to secure her own future; Mike puts a plan into motion for Gus.

episodes.title: Something Stupid
episodes.plot: Jimmy runs into a problem as he expands his business that only Kim can solve. Gus gets involved in Hector's medical care. Mike has to deal with a setback.

episodes.title: Coushatta
episodes.plot: Jimmy goes to great lengths to right a wrong, as Kim pulls out all the stops for a case; Mike lets his team blow off steam; Nacho receives a visitor.

episodes.title: Wiedersehen
episodes.plot: Jimmy attends his reinstatement hearing at the Bar Association; Nacho is forced to make the rounds with Lalo; Mike has cause to worry.

episodes.title: Winner
episodes.plot: Lalo tails Mike as he attempts to track down Werner; Jimmy and Kim invoke the memory of Chuck for the Bar Association appeal hearing.
